nodes.bodyText:
I've seen this pattern 3 times (counter, container and cache command). You can create a method in Context to do the resource change:
   public void changeResource(Class<? extends Resource> resourceClass, String childType, String childName) throws IOException {
      connection.setActiveResource(connection.getActiveResource().findAncestor(resourceClass).getChild(childType, childName));
      refreshPrompt();
   }

and the command would be invocation.getContext().changeResource(ContainerResource.class, CountersResource.NAME, name);

